Class AbstractJobAndTransactionalDropStrategy

  • java.lang.Object

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ReverseJobAndTransactionalDropStrategy

    public abstract class AbstractJobAndTransactionalDropStrategy
extends org.eclipse.papyrus.infra.gmfdiag.dnd.strategy.TransactionalDropStrategy
    A base class for DropStrategy using a Job running a Transaction. This class require an implementation of IJobAndTransactionForDrop, which provides methods of the life cycle. To use this class:
    • Provide an implementation of IJobAndTransactionForDrop
    • subclass this class and implements the createJobAndTransactionForDrop() method. The method return an instance of the previous class.
    • Register this class as a drop Strategy extension.
    The IJobAndTransactionForDrop implementation will be called as following :
    • Constructor
    • IJobAndTransactionForDrop.init(Request, EditPart)
    • IJobAndTransactionForDrop.canExecute()
    • IJobAndTransactionForDrop.jobPreprocess(IProgressMonitor)
    • IJobAndTransactionForDrop#jobRun()
    • IJobAndTransactionForDrop.jobPostProcess()

    This implementation subclass TransactionalDropStrategy in order to inherit the two methods TransactionalDropStrategy.getEditingDomain(EditPart) and TransactionalDropStrategy.getTransactionalEditingDomain(EditPart).
    The method doGetCommand(Request, EditPart) is disguarded and not used.
    The method getCommand(Request, EditPart) is reimplemented.
    Author:
    cedric dumoulin
